Question 4.4.1:

Q = Total product units

n = Market outlet number

d_i = Individual demand at outlet i for product units

p_i = Individiual product price at outlet i

What quantity (s) maximizes the revenue?

  Total revenue = sum_i_n [p_i*s_i]

  Constraint: sum_i_n [d_i] >= Q
                          
                          d > 0
  
                          p > 0

  Lagrange equation: L(Q, d_i, p_i, s_i, mu, lambda) = mu*sum_i_n [p_i*s_i] + lambda(Q-sum_i_n[d_i])

  Dual Lagrangian: q(p,s,mu,lambda,x) = mu*sum_i_n [p_i*s_i] + lambda*x

  A solution derivated: 

             dq(p, s, mu, lambda, x)/dp = mu*s

                                    = 0

             dq(p, s, mu, lambda, x)/ds = mu*p

                                    = 0

             dq(p, s, mu, lambda, x)/dlambda = x

                                         = 0

             dq(p, s, mu, lambda, x)/dx = lambda 

                                    = 0

   Answer: When items per store (s) equal the sale price (p).

           Also, an item amount (s) of zero units because management denied the regional business demands.  

What is the cutoff price for store demand?

  Total revenue = sum_i_n [p_i*s_i]

  Constraint: sum_i_n [d_i] >= Q
                          
                          d > 0

                          p > 0

  Lagrange equation: L(Q, d_i, p_i, s_i, mu, lambda, eta) = sum_i_n [p_i*s_i] + lambda(Q-sum_i_n[d_i]) + eta*(p-y)

  Dual Lagrangian: q(p,s,mu,lambda,x,eta,y) = sum_i_n [p_i*s_i] + lambda*x + eta*(p-y)

  A solution derivated:

             dq(p, s, mu, lambda, x, eta, y)/dp = mu*s + eta

                                                = 0

             dL(p, s, mu, lambda, x, eta, y)/ds = mu*p

                                                = 0

             dL(p, s, mu, lambda, x, eta, y)/dlambda = x

                                                     = 0

             dL(p, s, mu, lambda, x, eta, y)/dx = lambda

                                                 = 0

             dL(p, s, mu, lambda, x, eta, y)/dy = -eta*y
  
                                            = 0
   Answer: The cutoff price (y) is -p/(p-s) with more items per store (s) than price (p).

